      "content": "Labeling concerned parents as \"intolerant\" or \"outdated\" is a dangerous tactic that shuts down legitimate debate and ignores the fact that many families have a right to raise their children according to their own values. These parents are not missing something important; they are simply prioritizing traditional definitions of gender and family structure, which are deeply held beliefs that deserve respect, not dismissal. When schools dismiss parental concerns as intolerance, they are often trying to force a specific ideological agenda on families who haven't consented to it.",
